Location


















Arkwin Industries Inc



Public
Airline - Aviation





An airport hangar located at Strother Field, between the Kansas cities of ARKansas City and WINfield became the first home and namesake of Arkwin Industries. The company settled in Westbury, NY, where it attracts the best engineering, technical, and manufacturing talent available.Arkwin has grown from its humble beginnings in 1951 to a modern, multi-faceted organization. The vision of building a company on the cutting edge of aerospace technology has become a reality. Arkwin has earned a reputation for quality and reliability. It is a leader in custom-designed, precision hydraulic and fuel system components for civil and military fixed-wing aircraft, helicopters, spacecraft, turbine engines, and other special applications.Through selective team efforts with companies throughout the world, we continually attract new customers and diversify our product line. These international marketing agreements have resulted in the selection of Arkwin products by prominent aircraft manufacturers in Europe and the Far East.





Our People
Our people strive to provide the highest level of customer satisfaction. Arkwin has received many awards, in recognition of their efforts.
U.S. Department of Defense - National Small Business Contractor of the Year
GE Aircraft Engines - Quality Supplier and Achievement of Excellence Awards
Northrop Corporation - Collier Award, B-2 Industry Team Member and Corporate Excellence Award
United Technologies - Quality Award, NASA Space Program
Rockwell International - Excellence Award, NASA Space Program
Lockheed Aeronautical Systems - "ATTABOY" Award for Advanced Development Activity
Sikorsky Aircraft - Excellence Award
McDonnell Douglas Helicopter - Certified Supplier Award






